CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 14, 1967, pg. 16 reads: "Mr. and Mrs. Edward B. Lewis - Harris photo." Portion of accompanying article reads: "Mungo-Lewis Wedding Held in East Liberty - The St. James AME Church in East Liberty was the scene of one of the prettiest weddings of the early fall seasons when Mungo was united in marriage to Edward Burton Lewis.  The bride is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Logan Robert Mungo Jr., and the groom is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Ralph Lewis, all of East Liberty.  The Rev. J.G.Harris officiated at the double-ring nuptials."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Edward Burton Lewis wearing light colored dinner jacket, and bride Ms. Mungo Lewis wearing light colored boat neck dress with long lace sleeves and tiara with veil, cutting four tiered cake, in interior, possibly the Greater Pittsburgh Elks Lodge
